The paper focuses on cybersecurity education and game theory concepts, which are most relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of education and accessibility, which could fall under the cs.EDU (Computer Science Education) sub-category. The testing of the game with middle- and high school students suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, which could be relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of 3D printing, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
